HEADWORD: Chromotype
<hw>Chro"mo*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ color +
<ets>-type</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A sheet printed in colors by
any process, as a chromolithograph. See
<er>Chromolithograph</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A photographic picture in the natural
colors.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chromous</ent>⟦br⟧
